lay:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2010/jan/13/new-labour-purnell-election\">\"Labour must abandon its slick neoliberalism\"</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ReluctantFT-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ReluctantFT_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Pickard, Jim (16 May 2016). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://next.ft.com/content/86d7276a-f5a6-11e5-803c-d27c7117d132\">\"Jeremy Corbyn's reluctant man in the City - FT.com\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Financial_Times\" title=\"Financial Times\">Financial Times</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 June</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Financial+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Jeremy+Corbyn%E2%80%99s+reluctant+man+in+the+City+-+FT.com&amp;rft.date=2016-05-16&amp;rft.aulast=Pickard&amp;rft.aufirst=Jim&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnext.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F86d7276a-f5a6-11e5-803c-d27c7117d132&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AColin+Burgon\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colin_Burgon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.colinburgon.co.uk\">Colin Burgon website</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"ht